"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711802","Department for International Development","false","2017-03-23","<p>In 2015 over £300 million of UK Official Development Assistance (ODA) delivered by DFID was directed towards food aid. A further £200 million was delivered through multi-lateral organisations that work in humanitarian response to tackle poverty and hunger and £80 million directed towards Basic Nutrition programmes and Food Aid for Livestock.</p><p>In addition in 2015 over £600 million was spent on Material Relief for humanitarian responses, which includes cash transfers. This provides flexible assistance to those struggling in humanitarian crises, enabling them to buy food and meet the medical and shelter needs of themselves and their dependents.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-03-23T17:50:21.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711802/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711802/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711802/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-03-16","Food Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much of the UK's annual aid budget was spent on direct food aid globally in 2015.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","68226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711803","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-31","<p>​While we have not raised this specific issue with the Palestinian Authority, we regularly push the Palestinian leadership to tackle language that could incite violence or hatred, including anti-Semitic language. The UK abhors and condemns the use of anti-Semitic or any racist language.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-03-31T10:41:33.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711803/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711803/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711803/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-16","Imad Hamato","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions his Department has had with the Palestinian Authority on President Abbas' appointment of Imad Hamato as dean of the Al-Azhar institutes.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","68238"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711804","Department for International Development","false","2017-03-21","<p>The UK continues to lobby all parties to the conflict to facilitate commercial and humanitarian access, and is supporting the UN Verification and Inspection Mechanism, UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs and the UN Humanitarian Air Service to improve access for humanitarian agencies.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-03-21T18:00:37.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711804/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711804/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711804/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-03-16","Yemen: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that British-funded aid is not blocked at ports in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","68314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711805","Department for International Development","false","2017-03-21","<p>DFID will publish country anti-corruption strategies. In doing so DFID will want to ensure that we can take into account recommendations from the International Development Committee’s report and relevant aspects of the forthcoming UK Anti-Corruption Strategy. DFID continues to deliver against the country anti-corruption strategies and efforts to tackle corruption do not hinge on when they are published.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-03-21T18:01:16.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711805/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711805/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711805/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-03-16","Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, when her Department plans to release updated country-specific anti-corruption strategies.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","68318"
