"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711807","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-24","<p>The Department of Justice in Northern Ireland sponsors the Public Prosecution Service in Northern Ireland who investigate serious fraud submitted by the Police Service of Northern Ireland (PSNI). This is a devolved matter for the Northern Ireland Executive.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-03-24T14:58:34.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711807/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711807/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711807/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-03-16","Fraud: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many serious fraud cases have been investigated in Northern Ireland in the last five years.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","68228"
