"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711384","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-03-23","<p>I regularly meet with the FA and discuss a number of issues, including matters relating to integrity in football. The integrity of sport is absolutely paramount and we expect the highest standards of governance and transparency from our sports governing bodies.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-03-23T11:15:23.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711384/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711384/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711384/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-03-15","Football: Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent meetings she has with the FA on progress on its ongoing investigation into allegations of corruption.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","68203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711385","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-03-23","<p>It is a matter for the FA to investigate and charge participants when there is sufficient evidence of wrongdoing in the game. If this is of a criminal nature then they must present all evidence to the police for further investigation.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-03-23T11:13:18.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711385/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711385/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711385/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-03-15","Football: Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what types of assistance her Department has provided the FA to aid its investigation into allegations of corruption.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","68202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711386","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-22","<p>The Royal Navy is constantly evolving its recruitment marketing methods, using specific advertising campaigns, web based media, radio, social media, print and appearances at recruitment events.</p><p>To address the issue of recruitment to technical specialisations the Royal Navy employs a range of mechanisms to attract and develop such recruits including apprenticeship schemes and staged remunerative awards, as well as an active engagement in a University Technical Colleges affiliation programme aimed at assisting in the development of technically able young people.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-22T17:48:37.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711386/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711386/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711386/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Navy: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recruitment methods and incentives his Department is using to recruit engineers and warfighting specialists to the Royal Navy.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","68215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711387","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-20","<p>Information about the recycling of Royal Navy and Royal Fleet Auxiliary vessels in each of the last five years is contained in the following table:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of vessels</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Location of Recycling Facility</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>Turkey</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>Five in Turkey and one in UK</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>Turkey</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>Turkey</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>Turkey</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Following a series of open competitions, a number of former Royal Navy and Royal Fleet Auxiliary vessels have been recycled by a Turkish company, LEYAL Ship Recycling Ltd, over the last five years. These contracts were awarded because the company’s bid provided the best combination of technical capability and financial return to the Ministry of Defence.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-03-20T16:19:22.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711387/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711387/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711387/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Warships: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Royal Navy vessels have been scrapped in each of the last five years; and what the locations were of each scrap yard where those vessels were scrapped.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","68213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711388","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-22","<p>The Government publishes statistics on the operation of the Freedom of Information Act (FOI) 2000 within central Government, including timeliness, on a quarterly basis. The figures for requests received from July to September 2016 have been published at the following link:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/government-foi-statistics.</p><p>The figures for October to December 2016 are to be published shortly and those for January to March 2017 are yet to be compiled. FOI statistics are Official Statistics and are governed by the standards set out by the UK Statistics Authority (UKSA) in their Code of Practice. To publish information outside of the release timetable would be a breach of Protocol 2 of the Code of Practice for Official Statistics.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-03-22T17:38:39.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711388/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711388/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Ministry of Defence: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the average response rate was of his Department to individual Freedom of Information requests in each month since July 2016.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","68040"
