"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711390","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-20","<p>The Department remains on track to deliver the planned initial operating capability for Carrier Strike in December 2020.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-20T16:26:46.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711390/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711390/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Aircraft Carriers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when carrier strike capability will be operational.","false","Biography information for Mr Owen Paterson","North Shropshire","Mr Owen Paterson","68126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711391","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-23","<p>Full details of the Department's spend can be found in the Ministry of Defence Annual Report and Accounts, published at:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/mod-annual-reports</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-03-23T16:16:36.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711391/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711391/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Defence: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the change  has been in his Department's spend on (a) military and civilian staff, (b) equipment procurement, (c) equipment support, (d) infrastructure, (e) other and (f) consumption of inventory costs in the last six years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","68077"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711392","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-23","<p>Japan is an important ally for the UK, and there are growing levels of co-operation between the UK and Japan, which is entirely consistent with the Defence Equipment Co-operation Framework treaty signed by the two nations in 2013. Under the auspices of that treaty the UK and Japan continue to look at what areas of mutual interest and benefit there are, and those discussions may lead to new co-operative programmes. However, there are currently no missile related programmes in place beyond an on-going feasibility assessment of a joint new air-to-air missile programme, which is the potential development of a new variant of the Meteor beyond visual range missile incorporating some Japanese technology.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-23T16:15:37.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711392/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711392/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Japan: Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to expand missile-related industrial collaboration between the UK and Japan.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","68078"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711393","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-20","<p>The AJAX family of vehicles has a common base platform with six variants performing different roles and providing a number of options for the Army:</p><p>AJAX - reconnaissance and strike</p><p>ARES - armoured personnel carrier</p><p>APOLLO - repair</p><p>ATLAS - recovery</p><p>ARGUS - engineering reconnaissance</p><p>ATHENA - command and control</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-20T16:27:52.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711393/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711393/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the additional vehicle options are for the AJAX armoured vehicle programme.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","68076"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711394","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-23","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 24 February 2017 to Question 64890 to the hon. Member for Caerphilly (Wayne David).</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-23T16:19:48.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711394/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711394/answer","Hansard Extract - 24 February 2017 HOC 64890.docx","Hansard Extract - 24 February 2017 HOC 64890.docx","64890 - WQnA extract on Warship Shipbuilding","64890 - WQnA extract on Warship Shipbuilding","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711394/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when his Department will respond to Sir John Parker's Independent Report to inform the UK National Shipbuilding Strategy.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","68070"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711395","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-20","<p>The Ministry of Defence receives the revenue for the sale of any land it owns. Where land was used by the Department but owned by the Crown, any revenue received would be shared subject to an agreement between both parties. All revenues from land sales are reinvested in Defence.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-03-20T16:38:11.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711395/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711395/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711395/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Ministry of Defence: Land","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which Department receives the revenue for the sale of land that is (a) owned by his Department and (b) used by his Department but owned by the Crown.","false","Biography information for Wayne David","Caerphilly","Wayne David","68117"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711396","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-20","<p>The Ministry of Defence estimates that in 2015 there were 2.56 million UK Armed Forces veterans residing in households across Great Britain (GB), of which 270,000 were female veterans. Of those, we estimate that 127,000 female veterans were under 65 years old, and 143,000 were older.</p><p>The numbers of female veterans living in GB by region (for England only) and in Scotland and Wales is provided below, estimated to the nearest thousand.</p><p><strong>Number of Female Veterans </strong><br>North East - 11,000<br>North West - 28,000<br>Yorkshire and the Humber - 29,000<br>East Midlands - 16,000<br>West Midlands - 22,000<br>East of England - 19,000<br>London - 11,000<br>South East - 50,000<br>South West - 43,000<br>Scotland - 24,000<br>Wales - 18,000<br><strong>Total - 270,000</strong></p><p>Source: Office of National Statistics 2015 Annual Population Survey</p><p>The sum of the parts does not equal the total due to rounding.</p><p>Information on the numbers of female veterans by county and by Service is not currently available.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-03-20T16:40:45.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711396/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711396/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711396/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Veterans: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many female military veterans there are by (a) county, (b) region, (c) service and (d) age range.","false","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Mrs Anne-Marie Trevelyan","68120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711397","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-23","<p>It is too early to answer this question.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-23T16:14:37.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711397/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711397/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711397/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Japan: Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the value is of the UK-Japanese Joint New Air-to-Air Missile programme.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","68080"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711398","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-21","<p>The following bases in the UK are made available to the United States Visiting Forces:</p><p>RAF Alconbury</p><p>RAF Barford St. John</p><p>RAF Croughton</p><p>RAF Fairford</p><p>RAF Feltwell</p><p>RAF Lakenheath</p><p>RAF Menwith Hill</p><p>RAF Mildenhall</p><p>RAF Molesworth</p><p>RAF Welford</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-21T16:21:06.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711398/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711398/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","USA: Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will list all the US military bases sited in the UK.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","68108"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711399","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-20","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 12 January 2017 to Question 59239 to the right hon. Member for Mid-Sussex (Sir Nicholas Soames).</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-20T16:27:19.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711399/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711399/answer","59239_WQnA_extract_on_Type_26_Frigates.docx","59239_WQnA_extract_on_Type_26_Frigates.docx","59239 - WQnA extract on Type 26 Frigates","59239 - WQnA extract on Type 26 Frigates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711399/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when steel will be cut for the first Type 26 Frigate.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","68100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711400","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-23","<p>As at 17 March 2017, eight RAF and five Royal Navy pilots have been trained to operate the F35 Lightning aircraft.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-23T16:13:42.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711400/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711400/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711400/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many RAF pilots are trained to operate Lightning II jets.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","68093"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711401","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-23","<p>The F-35 Lightning programme will train sufficient pilots to deliver operational requirements.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-23T16:14:09.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711401/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711401/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711401/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many RAF pilots his Department plans to train to operate Lightning II jets in each of the next 10 years.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","68094"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711402","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-23","<p>The requested information could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p>The funding support which the Ministry of Defence provides for Combined Cadet Forces (CCF) units is based on the number of active cadets and the number of single Service sections within the unit, irrespective of whether the unit is in an independent or state school. State schools will receive the same funding support for their CCFs as fee-paying schools with the same number of cadets and single Service sections.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","68086","2017-03-23T16:17:09.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711402/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711402/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711402/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Armed Forces: Cadets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will list the combined cadet forces (CCF) that are in receipt of funding from the public purse that are based in fee-paying independent schools; and how much funding each such CCF receives.","false","Biography information for Michael Gove","Surrey Heath","Michael Gove","68099"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711403","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-23","<p>The requested information could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p>The funding support which the Ministry of Defence provides for Combined Cadet Forces (CCF) units is based on the number of active cadets and the number of single Service sections within the unit, irrespective of whether the unit is in an independent or state school. State schools will receive the same funding support for their CCFs as fee-paying schools with the same number of cadets and single Service sections.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","68099","2017-03-23T16:17:09.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711403/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711403/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711403/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Armed Forces: Cadets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which combined cadet forces (CCF) based in state comprehensive schools received funds from the public purse in the last three years; and how much of those funds each such CCF received in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Michael Gove","Surrey Heath","Michael Gove","68086"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711404","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-22","<p>The latest assessment of the cost to Defence of funding the four Ministry of Defence (MOD) sponsored Cadet Forces was for Financial Year (FY) 2013-14 when the total was £179.15 million. This figure includes a cost of £30.144 million for delivering the Combined Cadet Force in schools; however, the MOD does not hold information in a format which would allow a ready breakdown of this figure between fee-paying and state schools. The figures provided include the costs of wider training infrastructure, capital expense, regional support and Headquarters costs.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-03-22T17:47:44.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711404/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711404/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711404/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Armed Forces: Cadets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much of his Department's budget is spent on cadet forces; and how much of that amount is spent on (a) fee-paying and (b) state schools.","false","Biography information for Michael Gove","Surrey Heath","Michael Gove","68087"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711405","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-21","<p>We remain committed to tackling illegal trapping and poaching of birds in the Sovereign Base Areas (SBA).</p><p>Over the last twelve months we have arrested 55 poachers and conducted 39 police-led operations, seizing 3,031 items of netting equipment. Since November 2014, we have removed 61 acres of acacia at a cost of over €400,000.</p><p>The Sovereign Base Areas Administration will continue to work with the RSPB, BirdLife Cyprus and other Non-Government Organisations to do all they can to further reduce bird trapping within the SBA.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-21T16:23:33.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711405/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711405/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711405/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Cyprus: Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to prevent the illegal netting of wild birds within the sovereign base areas of Cyprus; and what steps are being taken to apprehend and prosecute those responsible for such acts.","false","Biography information for Sir Roger Gale","North Thanet","Sir Roger Gale","68092"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711406","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-22","<p>I am withholding this information as providing planned numbers would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces. However, the P8-A programme will train sufficient pilots to deliver operational requirements.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-22T17:39:24.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711406/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711406/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711406/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many pilots his Department plans to train to operate P8 Maritime Patrol Aircraft in each of the next 10 years.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","68095"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711407","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-23","<p>Testing of the computer systems used on the Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carriers has been undertaken both on-board, as well as at a dedicated shore-based mission system integration facility.</p><p> </p><p>HMS Queen Elizabeth is currently in her test and integration phase to demonstrate the readiness of her on-board systems to begin sea trials this summer.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-23T16:13:15.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711407/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711407/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711407/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","HMS Queen Elizabeth: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent assessment has been carried out on the resilience of computer systems on-board the HMS Queen Elizabeth.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","68091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711408","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-22","<p>There are currently seven RAF pilots who have been trained to operate P8 Maritime Patrol Aircraft, as at 20 March 2017.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-22T17:48:09.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711408/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711408/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711408/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many RAF pilots are trained to operate P8 Maritime Patrol Aircraft.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","68096"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711409","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-22","<p>The new service for enabling communication between Service personnel on operations and their families and friends is being introduced on 1 April 2017. Printed messages will still be provided to deployed personnel and any savings made will be reinvested into the improvement and development of the welfare services available to deployed personnel, such as increased Wi-Fi capabilities.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-03-22T17:47:14.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711409/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711409/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711409/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Armed Forces: Communication","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate his Department has made of savings accrued to the public purse by his Department no longer printing out messages for soldiers while on operation.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","68097"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711410","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-21","<p>The RAF is actively promoting careers in the engineering branch through: University Road Shows at universities with courses which focus on Science Technology Engineering and Maths (STEM); through specifically targeted marketing and media campaigns; and via Station events. The RAF is also offering attractive incentives such as sponsorship of STEM based university students, a 'Golden Hello' for Engineering Officers and the Continued Accelerated Promotion programme. Additionally, the RAF continues to engage with a number of national youth organisations to promote future careers in STEM.</p><p>The RAF is not encountering any difficulty in recruiting Intelligence Officers. Therefore, there is no focused recruiting or incentives for the intelligence branch outside of the current recruitment campaign.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-21T16:21:50.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711410/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711410/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711410/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Air Force: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recruitment methods and incentives his Department is using to recruit engineers and intelligence officers to the RAF.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","68132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711411","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-23","<p>As part of Joint Force 2025, the Royal Navy continues to develop and deliver the individual training that will enable personnel to operate and maintain safely all the equipment and systems required to run the Queen Elizabeth Class Aircraft Carriers.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-23T16:20:16.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711411/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711411/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711411/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Aircraft Carriers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to employ service personnel for specialist roles in the Carrier Strike Group.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","68133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711412","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-20","<p>I have interpreted “decommissioned” to mean withdrawn from service, in which case the following Royal Navy and Royal Fleet Auxiliary vessels have been decommissioned in the last five years:</p><p> </p><p>2012</p><p>HMS TURBULENT</p><p>HMS YORK</p><p>HMS LIVERPOOL</p><p> </p><p>2013</p><p>HMS EDINBURGH</p><p> </p><p>2014</p><p>HMS TIRELESS</p><p>HMS ILLUSTRIOUS</p><p> </p><p>2015</p><p>RFA ORANGELEAF</p><p> </p><p>2016</p><p>RFA BLACK ROVER</p><p>RFA DILIGENCE</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-03-20T16:18:28.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711412/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711412/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711412/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Warships: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Royal Navy vessels have been decommissioned in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","68186"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711413","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-23","<p>Discussions on the European Defence Fund have so far largely taken place in European Commission sponsored meetings with EU member states at official level. Much of the detail of the European Defence Fund is still being developed, however, we are confident that there will be no negative effects on UK-French equipment cooperation.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-23T16:19:02.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711413/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711413/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711413/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","France: Military Alliances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with his European counterpart on the European Defence Fund and its effect on plans for cooperation on defence equipment capability with France after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","68138"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711414","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-23","<p>The information is not held in the format requested. Information on the stationed location of UK Regular Service Personnel in Northern Ireland as at 1 January 2017 is given below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Army</p></td><td><p>2,070</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Air Force</p></td><td><p>60</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Royal Navy</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-03-23T16:21:15.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711414/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711414/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711414/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","Armed Forces: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people ordinarily resident in Northern Ireland are serving in the (a) Army, (b) Royal Air Force and (c) Royal Navy.","false","Biography information for Tom Elliott","Fermanagh and South Tyrone","Tom Elliott","68162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711415","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-22","<p>On 6 March 2017, at the Foreign Affairs Council (Defence), EU Member States agreed to establish the Military Planning and Conduct Capability (MPCC) for non-executive military missions only. The MPCC will be part of the existing EU Military Staff and its current Director General will also be the Director of the MPCC - there is no such post as EU Operations Commander in Brussels, these roles exist only in the field leading individual operations and missions. The UK has ensured that the MPCC to be set up is limited in size and scope, avoiding duplication with NATO and minimising costs. It will be for the remaining EU Member States to decide how the capability continues after we leave the EU.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-22T17:49:03.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711415/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711415/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711415/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-15","EU Defence Policy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with his European counterpart on the post of EU Operation Commander; and whether the UK plans to retain that post after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","68136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711416","Department for Education","false","2017-03-22","<p>We are increasing our annual investment in the free early years entitlements by £1 billion per year by 2019-20. This includes over £300 million a year for a significant increase to Government funding rates. We have also legislated to ensure that local authorities pass the vast majority of Government funding onto providers.</p><p> </p><p>This new investment is based on our ‘Review of Childcare Costs’, published in November 2015. The Review explicitly considered providers’ administrative costs and was described by the National Audit Office as “thorough and wide-ranging”.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, we are providing £2.15m to local authorities to improve their IT systems to allow more automation of the administrative requirements on providers.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-03-22T16:34:35.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711416/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711416/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711416/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-03-15","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if her Department will make provision for administrative costs incurred by nurseries as a result of extending the availability of free childcare.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","68164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711417","Department for Education","false","2017-03-27","<p>There are currently 430 open free schools, studio schools and university technical colleges. When at full capacity, these schools will create over 225,000 new school places. The Department provides new free school sites on either a lease or purchases basis, depending on the local market and specific requirements of each school, to ensure value for money. Up to August 2016, the Department spent £863 million on the purchase of 175 freehold sites.</p><p>For reasons of commercial confidentiality the capital costs of individual schools, including individual land purchase costs, are not disclosed before completion and overall costs are finalised. Capital funding for open free schools, UTCs and studio schools, where costs have been finalised, are published on Gov.UK at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/capital-funding-for-open-free-schools" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/capital-funding-for-open-free-schools</a>.</p><p>Additional finalised capital data is due to be published in the coming months.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2017-03-27T12:44:14.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711417/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711417/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711417/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-03-15","Free Schools: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much her Department has spent on land purchases for new free school sites in each fiscal year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","68176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711418","Department for Education","false","2017-03-29","<p>The Department for Education will invest over £24 billion on school buildings between 2016-17 and 2020-21 financial years, which includes funding for new school places, including the free schools programme, and funding to maintain and improve the condition of the school estate, including the Priority School Building Programme. The Department confirms annual funding allocations for specific programmes in the spring for the financial year ahead, based on the latest forecasts of programme delivery.</p><p>The Department’s Supplementary Estimate Memorandum for 2016-17 financial year sets the budget for the Priority School Building Programme as £1,030 million and that for Free Schools, University Technical Colleges and Studio Schools as £1,116 million. Spending plans for 2017-18 will be published alongside the forthcoming 2017-18 Main Estimate. The Memorandum is available here:</p><p><a href="https://www.parliament.uk/documents/commons-committees/Education/Department-for-Education-Supplementary-Estimate-2016-17-Memorandum.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.parliament.uk/documents/commons-committees/Education/Department-for-Education-Supplementary-Estimate-2016-17-Memorandum.pdf</a></p><p>Detailed spending plans for future financial years will be set out in future Main and Supplementary Estimates. This will include the Department’s plans for the £216 million funding for school maintenance referred to in table 2.1 of the Spring Budget 2017.[1]</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>[1] The £230 million referred to in item 3 of the table includes Barnett consequentials.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","68187 ; 68192","2017-03-29T14:11:48.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711418/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711418/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711418/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-03-15","Free Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the total amount of capital spending on the free schools programme will be in each of the next five fiscal years.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","68216"
